author: Lucy Craymer
title: Commodities Prices Are Heating Up on El Niño
text:
HONG KONG—The El Niño weather phenomenon is starting to push up prices for agricultural commodities as its impact spreads through key crop-growing regions in Asia and beyond.
Government forecasters in the U.S. and Australia have in recent weeks warned that El Niño could be the severest in nearly two decades. Late last week, the Japan Meteorological Agency said sea surface temperatures in the Pacific are “remarkably above normal” and...
